<inglise> COMMISSION REGULATION (EC) No 2042/98 of 25 September 1998 on special conditions for the granting of private storage aid for pigmeat </inglise>
<eesti> KOMISJONI M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (E&Uuml;) nr 2042/98 sealiha eraladustusabi andmise eritingimuste kohta 25. september 1998 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COMMISSION OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE KOMISJON, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa &Uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to Council Regulation (EEC) No 2759/75 of 29 October 1975 on the common organisation of the market in pigmeat (1), as last amended by Regulation (EC) No 3290/94 (2), and in particular Articles 4(6) and 5(4) thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse n&otilde;ukogu 29. oktoobri 1975. aasta m&auml;&auml;rust (EM&Uuml;) nr 2759/75 sealihaturu &uuml;hise korralduse kohta, (1) viimati muudetud m&auml;&auml;rusega (E&Uuml;) nr 3290/94, (2) eriti selle artikli 4 l&otilde;iget 6 ja artikli 5 l&otilde;iget 4, </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas intervention measures may be taken in respect of pigmeat if, on the representative markets of the Community, the average price for pig carcases is less than 103 % of the basic price and is likely to remain below that level; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: sealiha puhul v&otilde;ib v&otilde;tta sekkumismeetmeid juhul, kui &uuml;henduse t&uuml;&uuml;pilistel turgudel on sear&uuml;mpade keskmine hind madalam kui 103% baashinnast ning t&otilde;en&auml;oliselt j&auml;&auml;b sellest madalamaks; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the market situation has been characterized by a marked fall in prices below the level mentioned; whereas, in view of seasonal and cyclical trends, this situation could persist; </inglise>
<eesti> turuolukorda iseloomustab hindade m&auml;rgatav langus nimetatud tasemest madalamale; hooajalisi ja ts&uuml;klilisi suundumusi silmas pidades v&otilde;ib selline olukord olla p&uuml;siv; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas intervention measures must be taken; whereas these can be limited to the granting of private storage aid; </inglise>
<eesti> tuleb v&otilde;tta sekkumismeetmed; k&otilde;nealuse meetmed v&otilde;ivad piirduda eraladustusabi andmisega; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas it is appropriate, in view of the possible length of the present crisis in the pigmeat sector, to oblige operators to export the products under storage contracts in order to prevent them from coming back on the Community market after removal from storage; whereas these exports should take place according to certain provisions provided for in Commission Regulation (EEC) No 3444/90 (3), as last amended by Regulation (EC) No 3533/93 (4); </inglise>
<eesti> silmas pidades praeguse kriisi v&otilde;imalikku kestust sealihasektoris, on asjakohane kohustada ettev&otilde;tjaid eksportima ladustuslepingutega h&otilde;lmatud tooteid, et v&auml;ltida nende toodete tagasitulekut &uuml;henduse turule p&auml;rast laost &auml;ra viimist; k&otilde;nealune eksport peaks toimuma vastavalt teatavatele komisjoni m&auml;&auml;ruses (EM&Uuml;) nr 3444/90 (3) (viimati muudetud m&auml;&auml;rusega (E&Uuml;) nr 3533/93 (4)) esitatud s&auml;tetele; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Article 3 of Council Regulation (EEC) No 2763/75 (5) provides for the possibility of curtailing or extending the storage period; whereas, therefore, provision should be made to fix not only the amounts of aid for a specific period of storage but also the amounts to be added or deducted if this period is curtailed or extended; </inglise>
<eesti> n&otilde;ukogu m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 2763/75 (5) artikliga 3 n&auml;hakse ette v&otilde;imalus ladustamisaja l&uuml;hendamiseks v&otilde;i pikendamiseks; seet&otilde;ttu tuleks lisaks konkreetse ladustamisaja eest antava abi summale kindlaks m&auml;&auml;rata ka k&otilde;nealuse aja l&uuml;hendamise v&otilde;i pikendamise korral liidetavad v&otilde;i mahaarvatavad summad; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, in order to facilitate administrative and control work resulting from the conclusion of contracts, minimum quantities should be fixed; </inglise>
<eesti> lepingute s&otilde;lmimisest tuleneva haldus- ja kontrollitegevuse h&otilde;lbustamiseks tuleks kindlaks m&auml;&auml;rata miinimumkogused; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the security should be fixed at a level such as will oblige the storer to fulfil the obligations undertaken by him; </inglise>
<eesti> tagatis tuleks kindlaks m&auml;&auml;rata nii, et see kohustab ladustajat oma kohustusi t&auml;itma; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the measures provided for in this Regulation are in accordance with the opinion of the Management Committee for Pigmeat, </inglise>
<eesti> k&auml;esolevas m&auml;&auml;ruses s&auml;testatud meetmed on koosk&otilde;las sealihaturu korralduskomitee arvamusega, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> As from 28 September 1998 applications for private storage aid may be introduced in accordance with the provisions of Regulation (EEC) No 3444/90. </inglise>
<eesti> Taotlusi eraladustusabi saamiseks v&otilde;ib m&auml;&auml;ruses (EM&Uuml;) nr 3444/90 s&auml;testatud korras esitada alates 28. septembrist 1998. </eesti>
<inglise> The list of products which qualify for aid and the relevant amounts are set out in the Annex hereto. </inglise>
<eesti> Abi saamise tingimustele vastavate toodete loetelu ja asjakohased summad esitatakse k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse lisas. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Without prejudice to the provisions provided for in Article 3(4) of Regulation (EEC) No 3444/90, all the products under contract must be exported at the latest on the 60th day following the maximum contractual storage period, in accordance with one of the three possibilities provided for in Article 9(4) of the said Regulation. </inglise>
<eesti> Ilma et see piiraks m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 3444/90 artikli 3 l&otilde;ike 4 s&auml;tete kohaldamist, tuleb k&otilde;ik lepinguga h&otilde;lmatud tooted eksportida hiljemalt kuuek&uuml;mnendal p&auml;eval p&auml;rast maksimaalse lepingulise ladustamisaja l&otilde;ppu, kasutades &uuml;ht kolmest v&otilde;imalusest, mis on s&auml;testatud k&otilde;nealuse m&auml;&auml;ruse artikli 9 l&otilde;ikes 4. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> The provisions of Article 6(3) of Regulation (EEC) No 3444/90 apply mutatis mutandis to the unexported quantities. </inglise>
<eesti> M&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 3444/90 artikli 6 l&otilde;ike 3 s&auml;tteid kohaldatakse mutatis mutandis eksportimata koguste suhtes. </eesti>
<inglise> 4. </inglise>
<eesti> 4. </eesti>
<inglise> If the period of storage is extended or curtailed, the amount of the aid shall be adjusted accordingly. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui ladustamisaega pikendatakse v&otilde;i l&uuml;hendatakse, kohandatakse vastavalt ka abisummat. </eesti>
<inglise> The amounts of the supplements and deductions per month and per day are set out in columns 6 and 7 of the said Annex. </inglise>
<eesti> Liidetavad ja mahaarvatavad summad kuu ja p&auml;eva kohta on s&auml;testatud nimetatud lisa veergudes 6 ja 7. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> The minimum quantities per contract and per product shall be as follows: </inglise>
<eesti> &Uuml;he lepingu ja &uuml;he toote kohta on miinimumkogused j&auml;rgmised: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) 10 tonnes for boned products; </inglise>
<eesti> a) 10 tonni konditustatud toodete puhul; </eesti>
<inglise> (b) 15 tonnes for all the other products. </inglise>
<eesti> b) 15 tonni k&otilde;igi muude toodete puhul. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> The security shall be 20 % of the amounts of aid set out in the Annex. </inglise>
<eesti> Tagatis on 20% lisas s&auml;testatud abisummadest. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 4 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 4 </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall enter into force on the day of its publication in the Official Journal of the European Communities. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus j&otilde;ustub Euroopa &Uuml;henduste Teatajas avaldamise p&auml;eval. </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall be binding in its entirety and directly applicable in all Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus on tervikuna siduv ja vahetult kohaldatav k&otilde;ikides liikmesriikides. </eesti>
<inglise> Done at Brussels, 25 September 1998. </inglise>
